        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 6:16AM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 616 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
capable of producing a landspout near Kaplan, moving northeast at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lafayette, Crowley, Scott, Rayne, Kaplan, Duson, Maurice, Lyons
Point, Indian Bayou, Ridge, and Wright.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
